    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON EFA-12 - REPLACE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REPLACE</title>
        <svcproc id="hl0200605" svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>TIE ROD END REPLACEMENT</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect tie rod end (refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s02006_6.xml" xrefid="hl0200603">STEERING KNUCKLE DISASSEMBLY</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen clamp nut and unscrew tie rod end.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new tie rod end. Thread end into cross tube past the tube split (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200627">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200627" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200627.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Tie Rod Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach rod end to Ackermann Arm. Tighten to 165 - 230 ft-lbs. (224 - 312 N&#183;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200628">Figure 28</hotlnk>). Install cotter pin.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200628" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200628.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Torque Specifications</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust toe-in (refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s02006_16.xml" xrefid="hl0200606">TOE SETTING</hotlnk>). Tighten cross tube clamp
                    screw to 45 - 60 ft-lbs. (61-81 N&#183;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On tie rods with rotating clamp, position clamp with fastener away from beam.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
